text: Suomen Naisyhdistys, in Swedish Finsk kvinnoförening, is a Finnish women's rights organisation.Aura Korppi-Tommola (toim.): Tavoitteena tasa-arvo. Suomen Naisyhdistys 125 vuotta. SKS, 2009. It was founded in 1884, and is the oldest women's movement organisation in Finland. It is a member of the International Alliance of Women, that has general consultative status with the United Nations. ==References== Category:Feminist organisations in Finland Category:1880s establishments in Finland Category:1884 establishments in the Russian Empire Category:Voter rights and suffrage organizations
